body: Preliminary analysis: code that is not meant to be called for internal classes (`mysqli`, for instance) is called for internal classes. Need to investigate why that happens with your test suite.

I just came across `abstract class GenericTest extends TestCase implements ExtensionVersionProviderInterface` in your test suite. Using the `Test` suffix for abstract test case classes no longer works in PHPUnit 10.

While this may or not be related to the issue at hand, I would suggest that you rename your abstract test case classes to not have a `Test` suffix anymore. `TestCase` can be used instead, for instance.

Seems not enough: 
- I've renamed GenericTest class to GenericTestCase ( `abstract class GenericTestCase extends TestCase implements ExtensionVersionProviderInterface`)
- I've renamed all TestCase(s) files with TestCase.php suffix rather than just Test.php
- I've applied changes on all TestCase(s) : (i.e: `class MysqliExtensionTestCase extends GenericTestCase`)
- I've replaced all suffix in each `phpunit.xml.dist` file (`suffix="ExtensionTestCase.php"`)

But that gave almost the same results (with Composer installation)

#3 {main}
```

> > Not committed, just did locally for testing purpose !

> I need these changes in order to continue my debugging. 

I'll prepare a fresh environnement with changes on a new branch to avoid disturbing my stable `master` branch

My new branch `phpunit-10` (https://github.com/llaville/php-compatinfo-db/tree/phpunit-10) is availble :

- each commit represent changes I've applied from master branch 


Main `phpunit.xml.dist` configuration was migrate with `--migrate-configuration`

Old configuration file without migration is now `phpunit-9.xml`


If you want to have a fresh re-built database, you need to : 

- remove old file (if exists): `rm ~/.cache/bartlett/compatinfo-db.sqlite`
- create database schema: `bin/compatinfo-db db:create`
- initialize contents with all JSON data files : `bin/compatinfo-db db:init`
